Hello all Cheif Delphites!

I’m currently a member of FRC Team 93 and before kick-off we would like to share some of our best 3D printed electronics mounts for everyone to use this year whether that be for your radio, CANivore, or something more. Please look through this post and this thread and I can almost guarantee you’ll find something you like or might find at least a little nifty!

Radio Mounts -
RadioHolderV6 (mounted with Nylock Nuts)

drive.google.com

RadioHolderV6 (Nylock Nuts).step

Google Drive file.

RadioHolderV6 IMAGE1534×1258 430 KB

RadioHolderV6 (mounted with Nylock Nuts) - FULL ASSEMBLY

drive.google.com

RadioHolderV6 (Nylock Nuts) Full Assembly.step

Google Drive file.

drive.google.com

RadioHolderV5 (Countersunk Screws).step

Google Drive file.

RadioHolderV5 IMAGE1664×1290 629 KB

image1210×928 115 KB

93_RSL_Mount IMAGE1122×1076 230 KB

Ethernet Extension Holder - (We use an Ethernet extension to the very outside of our robot so direct-connecting Ethernet is easier than crawling inside the robot to wire into our RIO directly.)

drive.google.com

2023_1009_Cable_Matters_Ethernet_Extension_Holder.step

Google Drive file.

CANcoder secondary mount - This comes in two parts… A top and a bottom. The bottom part holds almost everything and mounts the CANcoder and the top piece holds it in place
CANcoder bottom housing -

drive.google.com

Bottom-Cancoder.step

Google Drive file.

CANcoder top housing -

drive.google.com

Top-Cancoder.step

Google Drive file.

CAN-Coder Mount IMAGE1120×796 294 KB

SparkMAX motor controller mount -

drive.google.com

SPARK MAX Motor Controller.step

Google Drive file.

SparkMAX Cover IMAGE1188×1126 107 KB

CANivore mount for RoboRIO - We no longer use a NavX so in it’s place we put our CANivore! It mounts to the same holes as the NavX -

drive.google.com

RioToCANivoreV2.step

Google Drive file.

RoboRIO-CANivore IMAGE1250×1354 90.6 KB

RoboRIO Port Cover - Hate having all that dust into those RoboRIO ports?!? ME TOO!!! Cover your Rio with some cool Team 93 Swag! -

drive.google.com

RioCoverV3.step

Google Drive file.

RoboRIO Cover - IMAGE1238×1380 454 KB

The CAN-hub for those who don’t fully get CAN-hub’s!!! This is a holder for these type of wire splicers that we occassionally used for a CAN-hub. Do I recommend this method of Star-CAN? Not really… Do I have the CAD model for it? SURE DO!

Type of Splices we used - https://www.amazon.com/Wire-Connectors-Solderless-Stripping-Connection/dp/B07114RK67/ref=m_crc_dp_lf_d_t1_d_sccl_3_1/136-3655436-7288606?pd_rd_w=H8J66&content-id=amzn1.sym.76a0b561-a7b4-41dc-9467-a85a2fa27c1c&pf_rd_p=76a0b561-a7b4-41dc-9467-a85a2fa27c1c&pf_rd_r=XY31ZWSRD2GA55WF1QVR&pd_rd_wg=K9yIY&pd_rd_r=f0b2977c-4219-4bf3-97b4-b847c1536a42&pd_rd_i=B07114RK67&psc=1

CAD model for it -

drive.google.com

NewCanHub.step

Google Drive file.

CANHub Image914×790 256 KB

Network Switch holder - Currently off the top of my head I do not remember or have the link to the Network switch. Next week (sometime around January 10th) I will update this post a little and link it in here in addition to the CAD model I have linked below.) -

drive.google.com

NetworkSwitchV6.step

Google Drive file.

NetworkSwitchV6 IMAGE762×666 222 KB

Raspberry Pi Case - This is a Raspberry Pi 4 Case that we’ve used on our robot and has been very consistent for us. -

drive.google.com

PiCaseV5.step

Google Drive file.

PiCaseV5 image1884×1288 514 KB

Nut/Screw Sorter for a few types - M4-M10 and 1/4 and 5/16 inch sizes of Nuts can be held by this piece (friction fit) and you can use them to test screw sizes and thread types of said sizes. -

drive.google.com

Nut and Screw Sorter V2.step

Google Drive file.

Nut and Screw Sorter IMAGE1010×1002 317 KB

It’s a hex adapter… Pretty much just what the file name is…

drive.google.com

am-3832_short 375H to 500H Adapter 500 long.step

Google Drive file.

SDS Swerve Shield Elite Guard - We use SDS MK4 swerve drive modules (not MK4I just MK4) and we use swerve shields on said modules. This comes with 3 parts.The two large, main shields - A connection bracket that connects at the corner of the two large, main shields - And a handle piece for easier grip of said main shields.
Some call it a cool project… I call it… the SDS Swerve Shield Elite Guard.
Main shield -

drive.google.com

Swerve_Shield_Plate_With_Handles (For-Swerve-Shield-Elite).step

Google Drive file.

Connection Bracket (to connect two shields) -

drive.google.com

Swerve_Shield_Bracket (For-Swerve-Shield-Elite).step

Google Drive file.

Handle for Swerve Shield Elite (screws into top holes) -

drive.google.com

HandleV3 (For-Swerve-Shield-Elite).step

Google Drive file.

Assembly STEP file -

drive.google.com

SDS Swerve Drive Elite Guard ASSEMBLY.step

Google Drive file.

SDS Swerve drive elite guard assembly Image1216×1008 427 KB

I worked on this entire post for over 4 hours just compiling files and images so If there are any issues with the links not downloading please let me know! Also, if you want to remix any part or anything please by all means do so and some credit to our team is always appreciated. If there are any other issues with any part or something not working right please by all means contact me by responding to this thread and if there are any questions with parts I would be more than happy to answer them as the descriptions I put are not the most detailed… I would like to thank our previous VP of Engineering on Team 93 Spencer W. as a lot of these designs would not be what they are today without his help in previous seasons.
Thanks again to the entire FRC and Chief Delphi community, and have a great kick-off!!!
- Dom H. from Team 93
